place.name: ROBESTON WEST
place.gazetteerText: ROBESTON (West), a parish in Haverfordwest district, Pembroke; 2½ miles N W of Milford r. station. Post-town, Milford-Haven. Acres, 1, 100. Real property, £1, 770. Pop., 159. Houses, 29. R. Hall is the seat of the Scourfields. The living is a rectory in the diocese of St. Davids. Value, £169. Patron, not reported. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
